Horse in beef products
Horse meat has been detected in cans of beef products, sold by two small British retail brands at low prices, the agency responsible for food hygiene announced today.
Routine testing revealed that the products, developed in January in Romania and sold by the Home Bargains and Quality Save chains, contained horse DNA of 1 to 5%.
