This has prompted all airlines to encourage passengers to buy directly from them instead of from an online travel agency.
However, Frontier has gone further in this area.
In September, it started offering only half miles of loyalty to customers who purchased their ticket via an online travel agency.
On Wednesday, she reduced miles premiums by 25% on a trip.
For example, a 1,000-mile border trip purchased from an online travel agency would make it possible to earn 250 miles.
