Congolese army chases M23 rebels
The Congolese army (FARDC) announced on Thursday that its units would hunt down the M23 rebels to their bases in the forests and mountains of North Kivu bordering Rwanda and Uganda.
The M23 appears to be about to be beaten after being driven from the localities of the north-east of the Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC), which it had controlled since the beginning of the insurgency 20 months ago.
"We will sue the M23 and accuse him wherever he hides because they are criminals," said Colonel Olivier Hamuli, FARDC spokesman, to Reuters.
We must not let them reorganize because they have been martyring the Congolese people for too long.
